  <header>
    <h1>¡Welcome, Typical Restaurants of Zaruma!</h1>
       <img src="img/zaruma.jpg" alt="foto" width="300">
  </header>

<h3 style="text-align: left;">On this gastronomic route, we will visit three of the most traditional restaurants in Zaruma.</h3>
  <section>
    <h2 style="color: rgb(162, 38, 38);">1. Cafetería Uno</h2>
    <img src="img/fotorestaun.jpg" alt="foto" width="300">
    <p>Our first stop is Cafetería Uno</strong>, it is located next to Miguel Sánchez School, in the center of Zaruma. This place was founded in 1982 and is known for its typical breakfasts and traditional snacks.</p>

    <h2 style="color: rgb(162, 38, 38);">2.	Cocada Bar </h2>
    <img src="img/cocadabar.png" alt="foto" width="300">
    <ul>
      <li>Our second stop is Cocada Bar, it is located under Radio Fuego, also close to the center of Zaruma. It is a small place where you can buy traditional sweets like cocadas, made with grated coconut and panela.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="color: rgb(162, 38, 38);">3. A Lo Criollo</h2>
      <img src="img/a lo ciollo.jpg" alt="foto" width="300">
        <p>Our third stop is A to Criollo</strong>, it is a restaurant founded in April 2024. It blends traditional and modern flavors in its typical Ecuadorian dishes. It is located right in front of Zaruma's central park, just a few meters from Banco del Ecuador and five minutes on foot from the coliseum.</p>
<h1></h1>
  </section>
